---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About AXIS"
  description="AXIS connects what's happening in the sky to what's happening on Earth — grounded in African ancestral wisdom traditions and the oldest star-tracking systems on the planet."
>
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-white mb-6">About AXIS</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      AXIS connects what&apos;s happening in the sky to what&apos;s happening on Earth.
      We write for people who don&apos;t know astrology — and don&apos;t need to.
      You bring the curiosity. We bring the translation.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Our analysis is grounded in African ancestral wisdom traditions — Dogon, Ifá, Vodou, Khemetic —
      and uses the actual positions of the stars, not the simplified version most Western astrology apps rely on.
      That distinction matters. It means our reads are rooted in thousands of years of sky observation,
      not a system that drifted off-course centuries ago.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      We also cross-reference what&apos;s in the sky with what&apos;s in the news — real geopolitical events,
      real economic shifts, real cultural moments. The goal is never to predict your fate.
      It&apos;s to give you a sharper lens on the time you&apos;re already living through.
    </p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
      Built by Travone Butler — full-stack engineer, AI systems architect, Houston TX.
    </p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
